<div>
  <h2> Simple batchload </h2>

  <div class="flexbox full_viewport_whitespace">
    <div class="item item1">
      <h3> Description and requirements </h3>

      <p> Creates asserted distributions (distribution records for taxa, not specimens, from published accounts).
        <ul class="no_bullets">
          <li>
            You must provide at least one of otu_name, otu_id, taxon_name, or name.
            If more than one is provided, otu_id will be used.
            The taxon_name column matches the OTU's taxon name label (cached).
            The name column first matches OTU name, then falls back to taxon name.
          </li>
          <li>
            You must provide at least one of (with priority in the given order):
            <ul>
              <li>
                geographic_area_id
              </li>
              <li>
                geographic_area_name - you may need to select your 'Preferred gazetteer' in the dropdown as well to restrict to a unique match on name
              </li>
              <li>
                country, state, county, if more than one provided all will be used to match and the finest recorded
              </li>
              <li>
                gazetteer_id - used only if none of the above geographic area columns are present
              </li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li>
            You must provide at least one of source_id, doi, citation, if more than one provided priority of use is source_id, doi, then citation. Citation text must match the 'cached' column of an existing source at /sources/list (matching ignores any &lt;i&gt;, &lt;/i&gt;, &lt;em&gt; and &lt;/em&gt; tags).
          </li>
        </ul>
      </p>
      <p>
        The upload file must:
        <ul>
          <li>
            <em>be a text file using <b>tab</b> separated values</em> (not comma-separated)
          </li>
          <li>
            include a header row naming the columns
          </li>
          <li>
            have unix line endings
          </li>
          <li>
            be utf-8 encoded
          </li>
        </ul>
      </p>

